# CodeQL-friendly structured logging

## Policy

When logging **externally influenced strings** or **stable operational identifiers** that CodeQL may treat as sensitive (for example **`cs/log-forging`**, **`cs/exposure-of-sensitive-information`**):

1. Prefer **`ArchLucid.Core.Diagnostics`** extension methods (**`SanitizedLoggerInformationExtensions`**, **`SanitizedLoggerWarningExtensions`** including **`LogWarningWithSanitizedUserArg`**, **`SanitizedLoggerDebugExtensions`**, **`SanitizedLoggerErrorExtensions`**, **`SanitizedLoggerHostLeaderElectionExtensions`**) instead of **`_logger.LogInformation`** / **`LogWarning`** / **`LogDebug`** with **`LogSanitizer.Sanitize`** repeated at feature call sites.
2. Add new message shapes by **adding a named extension method** beside existing helpers: sanitize immediately above the **`ILogger`** sink; keep any required **`// codeql[…]`** on that sink or the line immediately before it (**`docs/library/CODEQL_TRIAGE.md`**).
3. The **`LogSanitizer`** CodeQL pack covers **`cs/log-forging`** barrier modeling; Boxing through **`params object?[]`** may still require these helpers.
